definitions.definition: One who officially belongs to a group.

definitions.example: The I-beams were to become structural members of a pedestrian bridge.

definitions.definition: Part of an animal capable of performing a distinct office; an organ; a limb.
One of the propositions making up a syllogism.
A function or piece of data associated with each separate instance of a class.
The judge or adjudicator in a consumer court.
A part of a discourse or of a period, sentence, or verse; a clause.
Either of the two parts of an algebraic equation, connected by the equality sign.
A file stored within an archive file.
definitions.example: The zip file holding the source code of this application has 245 members.
